         <abstract id="aspace_2348e3e90f1eab640a9cfda6c35d429c">The papers contain two manuscripts. The first, "Plan for Raising Funds for Polish Relief", describes Newport's efforts to raise money for the Polish Relief Fund in 1940. The second, "The Saga of Pelorus Jack", is an unpublished fictional biography of a dolphin who reputedly escorted ships through Frenchmen's Strait in New Zealand in the 1880s and 1890s. Included is an incomplete manuscript, notes on dolphins and historical events related to the story, and correspondence, mostly with Carl C. Cutter</abstract>
